        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:33PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 932 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Bellview, or 29 miles northwest of Friona, moving
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bootleg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
